<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Will melee be useful beyond 20th</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:48 p.m. 26/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Will melee be useful beyond 20th<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1718" TARGET=_self>Re: Level differences in melee are too pronounced</A> (Galford Teveril[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I suspect that at mid levels and up it will prove quite difficult to kill another player that does not choose to stand and fight to the death. Groups may still be able to kill individuals but 1 on 1 at mid-high levels isn't going to work. Just my suspicions from previous testing.
<P>As for testing now, I'm going to test the system all the way up in levels. If there's a problem at 5-7, it might be a bigger problem at 10-12, or maybe not a problem at all. Only way to find out is to try it and document the results.
<P>&gt; Just one thing you need to keep in mind Black, nothing can be
<BR>&gt; really "tested" at level 5 or 7 for that matter. At
<BR>&gt; those low levels the characters are weak. It isn't until the
<BR>&gt; higher levels that I feel you should start testing that, because
<BR>&gt; all in all, we are not going to be playing as level 5 and 7 on
<BR>&gt; the PvP server forever, let alone all that long. I will say this
<BR>&gt; though, in phase 4 I killed a lot of people, most of them where
<BR>&gt; blue risky, but every now and then there was an even, gamble, or
<BR>&gt; tombstone. I was level 14 and had no problems with magic being
<BR>&gt; resisted (cept root), nor did I have any problems hitting the
<BR>&gt; people with mele I fought, even the tombs. I think what we
<BR>&gt; should be more concerned with is at level 50, whether or not
<BR>&gt; mele will even be usefull.
<BR>&gt; Galford Teveril of Covetous Crew
<BR>&gt; www.covetouscrew.org
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
